ast.name: bubble popper
ast.comment: A library to create bubble popper games

body.text: Let's create a board that we will hold the bubbles.
Start by calling the initialize action on the board.
You can tweak the speed at which bubbles fall down the screen by using the set physics action.
You can also set friction on individual bubbles to tweak their speed.
Gets the set of bad bubbles
Gets the total number of bubble popped, bad bubble popped and missed bubbles.

AV8SVUvuDwSv5I8uNZ2NeBQd.text: Call add bubble to register sprites as bubbles that need to be tapped.

PaLIe82N6JLOyN0YyHXLTQ0L.text: Call add bad bubble to register bubbles that should not be tapped.

SSL7FhmdLCAFt2RfkvKgxZbA.text: Use set pop sound and set bad pop sound to set the sounds that should be played when a bubble is popped.

h8KW3LUF2NduYlfyMEWw58wh.text: The library keeps a count of popped bubbles, bad popped bubbles and missed bubbles. Use score to retrieve those values.

dR3u46vgOCbbXGSbkxGy0H4g.text: Sets the sound that plays when a bubble is popped.

MLBu4bHRfAlCL0H5y9Thd8NY.text: Sets the sound that plays when a bad bubble is popped

QKhWT3KiVdnobSgWJ0Wrvynp.text: You can also add multiple bubbles at once using add bubbles.

gXDKmotlhzxo7Vr9AJjmmcLE.text: Let's create a simple bubble image.

oDiRrwDbiZvUe3Yvr4X4GtY3.text: Adds multiple bad bubbles at once.

MLBu4bHRfAlCL0H5y9Thd8NY.text: Sets the sound that plays when the user whacks a bad mole.

oDiRrwDbiZvUe3Yvr4X4GtY3.text: Adds multiple bad moles at once.
